  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To determine if an intensive cardiac rehabilitation program with periodic reinforcements
      improve the compliance/adherence to secondary preventive measures (physical exercise,
      mediterranean diet, tobacco abstinence, pharmacological treatment) after an acute coronary
      syndrome with or without ST segment elevation versus an standard cardiac rehabilitation
      program
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
